                    <span>Albert Speer, whose career blossomed during the Third Reich as Hitler's principal architect and culminated as Germany's Minister of Armaments and War Production from 1942 to 1945, has produced a rich and fascinating account of his experiences and encounters with many of the infamous personalities of the Nazi state. <P>For anyone who has even the slightest curiosity about the history of Germany between 1933 and 1945, THIS BOOK WILL HOLD YOU IN THRALL. Speer tells a very powerful and compelling story.</span>
                  
              
